  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-meatball-and-tomato-sauce-with-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Roll the <strong>sausage meat</strong> into 12 <span class=\"text-danger\">[24]</span> meatballs (clean hands are the best way!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-meatball-and-tomato-sauce-with-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>meatballs</strong> to the pan with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook, turning occasionally, for 4-5 min or until starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-meatball-and-tomato-sauce-with-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>tomato & mozzarella tortelloni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>tortelloni</strong> for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>tortelloni</strong>, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-meatball-and-tomato-sauce-with-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and slice (don't chop!) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and <strong>tomato paste </strong>in 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-meatball-and-tomato-sauce-with-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the meatballs are starting to brown, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong> and <strong>dried basil</strong> to the pan and cook for 30 secs further or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>tomato stock </strong>to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce has thickened slightly and the meatballs are cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-meatball-and-tomato-sauce-with-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Stir the <strong>drained tortelloni </strong>and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped parsley </strong>(save the rest for later!)<strong> </strong>into the sauce<strong> </strong>and give everything a gentle mix up until the pasta is nicely coated – this is your <strong>sausage meatball & tomato sauce with tomato & mozzarella tortelloni</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sausage-meatball-and-tomato-sauce-with-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> sausage meatball & tomato sauce with tomato & mozzarella tortelloni</strong> topped with the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and <strong>remaining chopped parsley</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
